{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775882890266,"sessionID":"ses_28521e6adffe1Zu4euF5TVpGfe","part":{"id":"prt_d7ade6c19001LPClrxjRRk3FqC","messageID":"msg_d7ade6288001Z7sPHWwv82Ek0l","sessionID":"ses_28521e6adffe1Zu4euF5TVpGfe","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882947660,"sessionID":"ses_28521e6adffe1Zu4euF5TVpGfe","part":{"id":"prt_d7adf4bef001cgvAe9tzohfHna","messageID":"msg_d7ade6288001Z7sPHWwv82Ek0l","sessionID":"ses_28521e6adffe1Zu4euF5TVpGfe","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-036228a5b4da495b9952aed434305abd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-032 — Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images) Delta Specification\n\n## AR Metadata\n- **AR ID**: AR-032\n- **Title**: Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images)\n- **Module**: docker\n- **Language**: Dockerfile\n- **Size**: S\n- **Status**: Implementation Required\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis delta specification provides comprehensive acceptance criteria for Dockerfile multi-stage builds with 3 images in the AgentCube project. It defines requirements for building AgentCube components using multi-stage Docker builds to optimize image size, build time, and security. The specification covers three distinct stages: builder, dependency, and runtime stages, with detailed GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios to ensure proper implementation of the multi-stage build pattern.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Multi-stage build structure with three stages\n\nThe system SHALL implement Dockerfile multi-stage builds with three distinct stages: builder, dependency, and runtime.\n\n#### Scenario: Dockerfile defines three FROM statements\n- **GIVEN** a Dockerfile for an AgentCube component\n- **WHEN** the Dockerfile is examined\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain exactly three FROM statements\n- **AND** the first FROM SHALL define the builder stage\n- **AND** the second FROM SHALL define the dependency stage\n- **AND** the third FROM SHALL define the runtime stage\n\n#### Scenario: Builder stage uses build tools\n- **GIVEN** the builder stage FROM statement\n- **WHEN** the builder stage is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL use an image with build tools (e.g., golang:1.21, node:18, python:3.11)\n- **AND** it SHALL include necessary build dependencies\n- **AND** it SHALL be named with AS builder\n\n#### Scenario: Dependency stage extracts runtime dependencies\n- **GIVEN** the dependency stage FROM statement\n- **WHEN** the dependency stage is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL copy artifacts from the builder stage\n- **AND** it SHALL extract only runtime dependencies\n- **AND** it SHALL be named with AS dependencies\n- **AND** it SHALL use a minimal base image (e.g., debian:bookworm-slim, alpine:3.18)\n\n#### Scenario: Runtime stage uses minimal base image\n- **GIVEN** the runtime stage FROM statement\n- **WHEN** the runtime stage is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL use a minimal base image (e.g., distroless, alpine, scratch)\n- **AND** it SHALL copy only necessary artifacts from dependency stage\n- **AND** it SHALL NOT include build tools or development dependencies\n- **AND** it SHALL be the final stage (no AS name required)\n\n### Requirement: Build artifacts transfer between stages\n\nThe system SHALL properly transfer build artifacts between the three stages using COPY --from.\n\n#### Scenario: COPY --from builder to dependencies\n- **GIVEN** the dependency stage\n- **WHEN** copying artifacts from the builder stage\n- **THEN** COPY --from=builder SHALL be used\n- **AND** only compiled binaries or packaged artifacts SHALL be copied\n- **AND** build artifacts SHALL be copied to appropriate locations (e.g., /app, /usr/local/bin)\n\n#### Scenario: COPY --from dependencies to runtime\n- **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n- **WHEN** copying artifacts from the dependency stage\n- **THEN** COPY --from=dependencies SHALL be used\n- **AND** only runtime dependencies and executables SHALL be copied\n- **AND** source artifacts (e.g., source code, build cache) SHALL NOT be copied\n\n#### Scenario: Dependency isolation in intermediate stage\n- **GIVEN** the dependency stage\n- **WHEN** processing dependencies\n- **THEN** the stage SHALL install and configure runtime dependencies\n- **AND** the stage SHALL NOT include source code\n- **AND** the stage SHALL prepare the final dependency structure for the runtime stage\n\n### Requirement: Layer optimization and caching\n\nThe system SHALL optimize Docker layer usage and leverage build cache effectively.\n\n#### Scenario: Dockerfile instructions are ordered for caching\n- **GIVEN** the Dockerfile structure\n- **WHEN** examining instruction order\n- **THEN** frequently changing instructions (e.g., COPY source code) SHALL appear later\n- **AND** stable instructions (e.g., RUN apt-get install) SHALL appear earlier\n- **AND** dependency installation SHALL be grouped into single RUN instructions\n\n#### Scenario: COPY of dependencies before source code\n- **GIVEN** the builder stage\n- **WHEN** copying files\n- **THEN** dependency manifests (package.json, go.mod, requirements.txt) SHALL be copied first\n- **AND** dependency installation SHALL run before copying source code\n- **AND** source code SHALL be copied after dependencies are installed\n\n#### Scenario: Multi-line RUN instructions are combined\n- **GIVEN** the Dockerfile\n- **WHEN** multiple related commands are needed\n- **THEN** commands SHALL be combined using && or \\\n- **AND** package installation and cleanup SHALL be in single RUN layer\n- **AND** intermediate build artifacts SHALL be cleaned up in same layer\n\n### Requirement: Image size optimization\n\nThe system SHALL produce minimal final images through effective multi-stage build usage.\n\n#### Scenario: Runtime image excludes build tools\n- **GIVEN** the final runtime image\n- **WHEN** inspecting the image\n- **THEN** build tools (gcc, go, node, python-dev) SHALL NOT be present\n- **AND** development dependencies SHALL NOT be present\n- **AND** build cache files SHALL NOT be present\n\n#### Scenario: Runtime image includes only necessary files\n- **GIVEN** the final runtime image\n- **WHEN** examining image contents\n- **THEN** only executable binaries SHALL be present\n- **AND** only runtime libraries SHALL be present\n- **AND** only configuration files SHALL be present\n- **AND** source code SHALL NOT be present\n\n#### Scenario: Multi-stage reduces final image size\n- **GIVEN** comparison between single-stage and multi-stage builds\n- **WHEN** measuring final image sizes\n- **THEN** the multi-stage build SHALL produce a smaller image\n- **AND** the size reduction SHALL be significant (at least 50% smaller than single-stage)\n- **AND** the builder and dependency stages SHALL not be included in final image\n\n### Requirement: Security hardening in multi-stage builds\n\nThe system SHALL implement security best practices through multi-stage build structure.\n\n#### Scenario: Runtime image uses distroless or minimal base\n- **GIVEN** the runtime stage base image\n- **WHEN** examining the base image\n- **THEN** the base image SHALL be distroless or minimal (e.g., alpine, scratch)\n- **AND** the base image SHALL NOT include package managers (apt, apk, yum)\n- **AND** the base image SHALL have minimal attack surface\n\n#### Scenario: Non-root user configuration\n- **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n- **WHEN** configuring the container user\n- **THEN** a non-root user SHALL be created with USER instruction\n- **AND** the non-root user SHALL be used to run the application\n- **AND** files SHALL be owned by the non-root user with appropriate permissions\n\n#### Scenario: Security context configuration\n- **GIVEN** the Dockerfile\n- **WHEN** examining security configurations\n- **THEN** file permissions SHALL be restrictive (e.g., 755, 644)\n- **AND** sensitive files SHALL NOT be included in image\n- **AND** no secrets or credentials SHALL be embedded in the image\n\n### Requirement: Component-specific multi-stage builds\n\nThe system SHALL implement appropriate multi-stage builds for each AgentCube component.\n\n#### Scenario: Controller Manager multi-stage build\n- **GIVEN** the Controller Manager Dockerfile\n- **WHEN** the build is executed\n- **THEN** the builder stage SHALL use golang:1.21\n- **AND** the dependency stage SHALL extract Go runtime dependencies\n- **AND** the runtime stage SHALL use gcr.io/distroless/static-debian11\n- **AND** the final image SHALL contain only the compiled binary\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager multi-stage build\n- **GIVEN** the Workload Manager Dockerfile\n- **WHEN** the build is executed\n- **THEN** the builder stage SHALL use golang:1.21\n- **AND** the dependency stage SHALL extract Go runtime dependencies\n- **AND** the runtime stage SHALL use gcr.io/distroless/static-debian11\n- **AND** the final image SHALL contain only the compiled binary\n\n#### Scenario: Router multi-stage build\n- **GIVEN** the Router Dockerfile\n- **WHEN** the build is executed\n- **THEN** the builder stage SHALL use golang:1.21\n- **AND** the dependency stage SHALL extract Go runtime dependencies\n- **AND** the runtime stage SHALL use gcr.io/distroless/static-debian11\n- **AND** the final image SHALL contain only the compiled binary\n\n#### Scenario: Component build consistency\n- **GIVEN** all AgentCube component Dockerfiles\n- **WHEN** comparing the Dockerfile structures\n- **THEN** all components SHALL use the same multi-stage pattern\n- **AND** all components SHALL use the same Go version\n- **AND** all components SHALL use the same runtime base image\n\n### Requirement: Build arguments and versioning\n\nThe system SHALL support build arguments for version control and customization.\n\n#### Scenario: Build arguments for Go version\n- **GIVEN** the Dockerfile\n- **WHEN** ARG instructions are used\n- **THEN** GO_VERSION SHALL be defined as an ARG\n- **AND** GO_VERSION SHALL have a default value (e.g., 1.21)\n- **AND** GO_VERSION SHALL be used in FROM statements\n\n#### Scenario: Build arguments for component version\n- **GIVEN** the Dockerfile\n- **WHEN** ARG instructions are used\n- **THEN** COMPONENT_VERSION SHALL be defined as an ARG\n- **AND** COMPONENT_VERSION SHALL be used for labeling\n- **AND** COMPONENT_VERSION SHALL be used for version-specific build steps\n\n#### Scenario: Labels for image metadata\n- **GIVEN** the Dockerfile\n- **WHEN** LABEL instructions are present\n- **THEN** maintainer label SHALL be set\n- **AND** version label SHALL be set\n- **AND** description label SHALL be set\n- **AND** labels SHALL be consistent across components\n\n### Requirement: Health and readiness checks\n\nThe system SHALL include health and readiness checks in the runtime stage.\n\n#### Scenario: Health check endpoint configuration\n- **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n- **WHEN** HEALTHCHECK instruction is present\n- **THEN** HEALTHCHECK SHALL be configured\n- **AND** health check interval SHALL be specified (e.g., --interval=30s)\n- **AND** health check timeout SHALL be specified (e.g., --timeout=3s)\n- **AND** health check retries SHALL be specified (e.g., --retries=3)\n\n#### Scenario: Health check command uses appropriate protocol\n- **GIVEN** the HEALTHCHECK instruction\n- **WHEN** examining the health check command\n- **THEN** the command SHALL use curl or wget (if available)\n- **OR** the command SHALL use a built-in health endpoint\n- **AND** the command SHALL check the component's health endpoint (e.g., /healthz, /health)\n\n### Requirement: Multi-platform build support\n\nThe system SHALL support multi-platform builds through appropriate base image selection.\n\n#### Scenario: Base images support multiple architectures\n- **GIVEN** the Dockerfile\n- **WHEN** selecting base images\n- **THEN** builder stage base image SHALL support multi-arch (e.g., golang:1.21)\n- **AND** dependency stage base image SHALL support multi-arch (e.g., debian:bookworm-slim)\n- **AND** runtime stage base image SHALL support multi-arch (e.g., distroless)\n- **AND** images SHALL be buildable for linux/amd64 and linux/arm64\n\n#### Scenario: Cross-compilation in builder stage\n- **GIVEN** the builder stage\n- **WHEN** building for different architectures\n- **THEN** the build process SHALL support cross-compilation\n- **AND** GOARCH and GOOS environment variables SHALL be respected\n- **AND** the binary SHALL be compiled for the target architecture\n\n### Requirement: Build context and .dockerignore\n\nThe system SHALL optimize build context using .dockerignore file.\n\n#### Scenario: .dockerignore excludes unnecessary files\n- **GIVEN** the .dockerignore file\n- **WHEN** examining its contents\n- **THEN** .git/ directory SHALL be excluded\n- **AND** README.md SHALL be excluded\n- **AND** *.md files SHALL be excluded\n- **AND** test files SHALL be excluded (e.g., *_test.go)\n- **AND** .dockerignore file SHALL be excluded\n\n#### Scenario: Build context is minimal\n- **GIVEN** the Docker build command\n- **WHEN** the build context is analyzed\n- **THEN** only necessary files SHALL be included in build context\n- **AND** large unnecessary files SHALL be excluded via .dockerignore\n- **AND** build context size SHALL be minimized\n\n### Requirement: Entrypoint and command configuration\n\nThe system SHALL properly configure entrypoint and command in the runtime stage.\n\n#### Scenario: Entrypoint uses the compiled binary\n- **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n- **WHEN** ENTRYPOINT instruction is set\n- **THEN** ENTRYPOINT SHALL point to the compiled binary\n- **AND** the binary path SHALL be absolute (e.g., /app/controller-manager)\n- **AND** the binary SHALL be executable\n\n#### Scenario: CMD supports default arguments\n- **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n- **WHEN** CMD instruction is set\n- **THEN** CMD SHALL provide default arguments\n- **AND** default arguments SHALL be sensible for the component\n- **AND** CMD arguments can be overridden at runtime\n\n#### Scenario: Entrypoint script for initialization (optional)\n- **GIVEN** the runtime stage with an entrypoint script\n- **WHEN** an entrypoint script is used\n- **THEN** the script SHALL be copied from dependency stage\n- **AND** the script SHALL be executable\n- **AND** the script SHALL perform necessary initialization\n- **AND** the script SHALL exec the main binary at the end\n\n### Requirement: Cache and volume configuration\n\nThe system SHALL configure appropriate cache mounts and volumes for build optimization.\n\n#### Scenario: Build cache for Go modules\n- **GIVEN** the builder stage\n- **WHEN** building Go dependencies\n- **THEN** --mount=type=cache,target=/go/pkg/mod SHALL be used for go mod download\n- **AND** build cache SHALL persist across builds\n- **AND** dependency download time SHALL be reduced\n\n#### Scenario: Build cache for Go build\n- **GIVEN** the builder stage\n- **WHEN** building the Go binary\n- **THEN** --mount=type=cache,target=/root/.cache/go-build SHALL be used for go build\n- **AND** incremental builds SHALL be faster\n- **AND** compiled object files SHALL be cached\n\n### Requirement: Reproducible builds\n\nThe system SHALL support reproducible builds through proper Dockerfile practices.\n\n#### Scenario: Fixed versions in base images\n- **GIVEN** the Dockerfile\n- **WHEN** specifying base images\n- **THEN** base images SHALL use specific tags (e.g., golang:1.21.5)\n- **OR** base images SHALL use digests for complete reproducibility\n- **AND** latest tag SHALL NOT be used\n\n#### Scenario: Deterministic build process\n- **GIVEN** the Dockerfile\n- **WHEN** examining build instructions\n- **THEN** time and random factors SHALL be minimized\n- **AND** build timestamps SHALL be normalized if possible\n- **AND** the build SHALL produce identical outputs given same inputs\n\n### Requirement: Documentation and comments\n\nThe system SHALL provide clear documentation within the Dockerfile.\n\n#### Scenario: Dockerfile has descriptive comments\n- **GIVEN** the Dockerfile\n- **WHEN** examining comments\n- **THEN** each stage SHALL have a comment describing its purpose\n- **AND** complex build steps SHALL have explanatory comments\n- **AND** non-obvious COPY commands SHALL have comments\n\n#### Scenario: Dockerfile follows best practices\n- **GIVEN** the Dockerfile\n- **WHEN** reviewing against Dockerfile best practices\n- **THEN** .dockerignore SHALL be present\n- **AND** instructions SHALL be ordered for optimal caching\n- **AND** layers SHALL be minimized\n- **AND** multi-stage build SHALL be used effectively\n- **AND** security best practices SHALL be followed\n\n---\n\n## Backward Compatibility\n\nThis delta specification defines multi-stage Dockerfile builds for the AgentCube project. The multi-stage builds are an optimization over existing single-stage builds and produce the same runtime images with improved efficiency and security. The final runtime images maintain compatibility with existing deployments, as they contain the same binaries and dependencies.\n\n## Dependencies\n\nThis delta specification depends on:\n- Docker 20.10+ (for multi-stage build support)\n- Go 1.21+ (for building AgentCube components)\n- Base design document: `design.md`\n- Base specification document: `deployment/spec.md`\n- AR: AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values (for image configuration)\n\n## Breaking Changes\n\nNone. This delta specification defines an optimized build process using multi-stage Docker builds. The final runtime images remain compatible with existing deployments, and the build process change does not affect runtime behavior or API compatibility.\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n1. **Minimal Runtime Images**: Using distroless or minimal base images reduces the attack surface by excluding package managers, shells, and unnecessary tools.\n2. **No Secrets in Images**: Multi-stage builds ensure no secrets or credentials are embedded in the final image, as secrets are only used in the builder stage and never copied to runtime.\n3. **Non-Root Execution**: The runtime stage runs as a non-root user, reducing the impact of container escape vulnerabilities.\n4. **Limited Permissions**: File permissions are restrictive, and the container has minimal privileges.\n5. **Reproducible Builds**: Using specific image versions and digests ensures reproducible, verifiable builds.\n6. **Build Isolation**: The builder and dependency stages are not included in the final image, isolating build-time dependencies.\n7. **CVE Scanning**: Minimal images are easier to scan for vulnerabilities and have fewer CVEs to manage.\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Build Tests\n- Verify multi-stage builds complete successfully for all components\n- Verify build artifacts are correctly transferred between stages\n- Verify final images contain only necessary files\n- Verify build cache improves incremental build times\n\n### Image Size Tests\n- Measure final image size for each component\n- Compare with single-stage build size\n- Verify size reduction meets expectations (>50% reduction)\n- Verify builder and dependency stages are not in final image\n\n### Security Tests\n- Scan final images for CVEs using tools like Trivy or Snyk\n- Verify runtime images use distroless or minimal base\n- Verify no build tools are present in runtime images\n- Verify non-root user is configured correctly\n- Verify no secrets or credentials in final image\n\n### Functional Tests\n- Run containers built with multi-stage Dockerfiles\n- Verify containers start and run correctly\n- Verify health checks work as expected\n- Verify components can communicate with each other\n- Verify all functionality works as expected\n\n### Multi-Platform Tests\n- Build images for linux/amd64\n- Build images for linux/arm64\n- Verify images run correctly on both architectures\n- Verify cross-compilation works correctly\n\n### Cache Tests\n- Verify Go module cache works correctly\n- Verify Go build cache works correctly\n- Measure cache hit/miss rates\n- Verify incremental builds are faster\n\n### Reproducibility Tests\n- Build the same image twice and compare\n- Verify images are identical using digests\n- Verify build output is deterministic\n- Verify using image tags and digests produces reproducible results\n\n### Integration Tests\n- Test multi-stage builds in CI/CD pipeline\n- Verify builds work with Docker BuildKit\n- Verify builds work with Buildah (if applicable)\n- Verify image signing and verification (if implemented)","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775882947642,"end":1775882947657}}}}
